{
  "name": "Claims Investigation Triage",
  "domain": "insurance special investigations",
  "context": "A carrier's special-investigations unit picks which of 180 model-flagged claims to investigate this month across four lines of business. Recovery, hours, and friction pull in different directions: the best recovery-per-hour ratios sit on borderline claims where investigating a legitimate customer costs goodwill. A quarterly recovery target and a hard hours budget couple the picks \u2014 the plan must earn the target inside the capacity \u2014 under per-line concentration caps and four regulator-mandated referrals.",
